						<summary>

						<p>This is built in at the beginning of each line. This also like the two inscriptions above seem to be assignable to <hi rend="bold">Parāntaka I</hi>, as the writing resembles that of No. 29 of 1907 which is a clear record of his. It records a gift of 93 sheep for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple.</p>						

